	   <tr><td colspan=2>Bards are harder to play well.&nbsp;&nbsp;Once you get to higher levels (and like everyone else) need to group, how you play depends on the composition of the group.  If you get it wrong you will die alot.  It is difficult learning different styles and knowing when to use each - but very rewarding when you get it right.  Don't expect to make witty comments whilst fighting as you will be too busy hitting hot keys and swapping weapons / instruments.  I love to play a bard it is great fun.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
